    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  PD Group:

               -  Clinically definite PD

               -  40-70 years old

               -  Hoehn and Yahr stage I,II,III

               -  Currently treated with Levodopa/carbidopa

          -  Control Group:

               -  40-70 years old

               -  Spouses of PD Group preferred

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  PD Group and Control Group:

               -  Significant neurological problems

               -  Significant current psychiatric diagnoses

               -  Mini Mental Status Exam score &lt; 24 (MMSE)

               -  Any significant abnormality on brain imaging

               -  MPTP exposure

               -  Control Participants met the same exclusion criteria described above as well as a
                  biological family history of PD
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
